title: For Sale:  NEW Yugoslavian Yugo AK M70AB2 underfolder AK-47 with high capacity magazines, sling and historic parts
postcontent:
You are looking at a NEW Century Arms Inc. Yugoslavian AK-47 variant Model M70AB2 with underfolding/underfolder stock and polymer furniture chambered in 7.62x39mm. It comes with 2 Master Molder (aka Thermold) Military/LE Only-marked (see photo) 48 round magazines and 1 Tapco Intrafuse Polymer 30 round magazine.

The AK is marked ZASTAVA-KRAGUJEVAC YUGOSLAVIA on the rear sight block (see photo). This rifle is built using the RPK style trunion that is very heavy duty. A characteristic of this trunion is that you can see bulges on the side of the receiver and it is the strongest one you can use. The bolt carrier group is polished and not the cheaply painted ones. The barrel is excellent with no pitting and strong rifling.

The receiver is made by DC Industries and sold by Century Arms, Inc as the M70AB2. Both companies names are stamped into the receiver along with the model, serial number and caliber (7.62x39mm). This is one of the best and most robust US-made stamped receivers right up there with Nodak-Spud. The steel used in this receiver is 1.6mm thick, whereas most US made receivers are usually 1mm and if you're lucky you will find some that are 1.5mm thick.

Additionally, this package includes 3 high capacity magazines. 2 Master Molder 48 round magazines made of a strong polymer. These magazines were made exclusively for the Canadian military by Master Molder of Wilson, NC (also known as Thermold later on). These magazines are very strong and practically indestructible. I use them in all of my AK variants with no problems or FTF, etc. I am also including a Tapco Intrafuse 30 rd polymer magazine. These are very popular and have been around a long time. They are a strong polymer and use a steel floorplate. All of these magazines are Made in the USA and count as 922r compliant parts. The rifle comes with the Century Arms factory black polymer handguards and contoured finger groove pistol grip. The folding stock operates very smoothly and is very tight. Does not wiggle/rattle/wobble at all. I am also including a NEW surplus Black Nylon Web Sling with leather frogs.

If you are an AK or SOVIET/USSR era COLLECTOR or HISTORY BUFF you are going to love this part

I am also including a set of original issue Yugoslavian furniture that was recovered from the Yugoslav Wars of the 1990's (Serbia-Bosnia Conflicts, etc.), often mislabeled as the (modern) Balkan Wars. These are very cool and unique as they have what is called "TRENCH ART" on them. Basically, when the soldiers weren't fighting or were holed up in a trench, etc. the soldiers would carve family names, initials, crests, designs and various expressive lettering and emblems onto their wood furniture and plastic pistol grip to personalize their issued rifle. The furniture also shows signs of use from combat and could probably tell some great stories if it talked.(see photos for more detail)

Contact via e-mail here or call/text    7 6 zero -  7 nine 2   -  0 two zero 4

May consider trades of EQUAL or GREATER value ONLY.   Not interested in hunting rifles
